Measured data and alarm limits.Data description:
Duration of phototherapy, Dur PT
The value is transmitted using 4 ASCII encoded digits HHMM. The two left most digits, i.e. HH, resemble the full hours of duration, the two right most digits, i.e. MM, resemble the duration in minutes since the last full hour duration. If duration is less than 1 hour, then the first two digits are both Ascii encoded '0'. Both fields (HH and MM) are padded with a leading, ASCII encoded '0', if necessary, i.e., if the duration is less than 10 hours, HH is zero padded and if the duration since the last full hour is less then 10 minutes, then MM is zero padded.
A value of 9959 means duration took 99 hours and 59 minutes or longer.
